477
00:31:02,845 --> 00:31:07,204
- Special consultant to the president.
- I gotta say it.

478
00:31:07,558 --> 00:31:11,404
These notes on the White House librarian,
are they accurate?

479
00:31:12,271 --> 00:31:14,689
- The notes, are they accurate?
- Give me a second.

480
00:31:14,690 --> 00:31:15,982
- Yes.
- I want a new page.

481
00:31:15,983 --> 00:31:20,701
Okay, look, I'll have a reporter
out to talk to you this afternoon.

482
00:31:23,824 --> 00:31:26,993
Let's take it in
and show it to Howie Simons.

483
00:31:26,994 --> 00:31:29,495
We've gotta start moving
on this now. Come on, now.

484
00:31:29,496 --> 00:31:31,372
Hey, Mr. Bradlee.

485
00:31:31,373 --> 00:31:35,886
Get the artwork
on that Grant Porter piece.

486
00:31:37,296 --> 00:31:40,423
- Okay, let's have it. Mm-hm.
- Yeah, here you are, Ben.

487
00:31:40,424 --> 00:31:43,050
It's a good, solid piece
of American journalism...

488
00:31:43,051 --> 00:31:46,334
...that the New York Times doesn't have.

489
00:32:09,786 --> 00:32:13,539
You haven't got it. A librarian and
a secretary saying Hunt looked at a book.

490
00:32:13,540 --> 00:32:14,749
Not good enough.

491
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:17,752
A White House aide told me
Hunt was investigating Kennedy.

492
00:32:17,753 --> 00:32:19,795
Who was it?

493
00:32:19,796 --> 00:32:22,215
Who was it?
You want the name, you mean?

494
00:32:22,216 --> 00:32:26,831
- No, how senior, how high up?
- I don't know titles.

495
00:32:39,566 --> 00:32:41,317
"Showed a special interest in...."

496
00:32:41,318 --> 00:32:43,778
We said the White House
was investigating Kennedy.

497
00:32:43,779 --> 00:32:46,948
- "Showed a special interest in."
- The story's stronger than that.

498
00:32:46,949 --> 00:32:49,992
The White House librarian says
Hunt checked out a lot of books.

499
00:32:49,993 --> 00:32:53,246
- A secretary in Colson's office said Hunt...
- All right, Carl. Carl.

500
00:32:53,247 --> 00:32:56,529
Ben, that's a Page 1 story.

501
00:32:56,750 --> 00:32:58,339
Stick it inside someplace.

502
00:33:00,170 --> 00:33:04,888
This is a goddamn important story. It....

503
00:33:08,303 --> 00:33:11,380
Get some harder information next time.

504
00:33:15,644 --> 00:33:18,729
Asshole. Bradlee's just sticking up
for the Kennedys.

505
00:33:18,730 --> 00:33:20,773
- We didn't have it.
- Bullshit. We had it.

506
00:33:20,774 --> 00:33:22,817
- We didn't.
- Why didn't you say something?

507
00:33:22,818 --> 00:33:26,781
You think bitching about it
is gonna get the story where we want it?

508
00:33:27,573 --> 00:33:29,983
Throw it in the can.

509
00:34:00,397 --> 00:34:03,577
- Yes?
- This is Woodward.

510
00:34:04,818 --> 00:34:06,694
I wanna talk about Watergate.

511
00:34:06,695 --> 00:34:11,157
- I know that the atmos...
- We're not going to talk about that subject.

512
00:34:11,825 --> 00:34:15,703
- Well, we talked about Wallace.
- But this is different.

513
00:34:15,704 --> 00:34:19,915
That was about the shooting
of a man running for president.

514
00:34:19,916 --> 00:34:22,835
- This is different.
- How?

515
00:34:22,836 --> 00:34:26,477
Not about this story. Don't call me again.

516
00:34:30,594 --> 00:34:33,638
The stewardess hostages were released.

517
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,556
The passengers, numbering 113...

518
00:34:35,557 --> 00:34:37,516
...were released in Philadelphia.

519
00:34:37,517 --> 00:34:41,562
Things are warming up in Reykjavik, where
Bobby Fischer forfeited the second game...

520
00:34:41,563 --> 00:34:45,733
...of that $250,000
world-championship chess match...

521
00:34:45,734 --> 00:34:47,860
...with the Russian champion
Boris Spassky.

522
00:34:47,861 --> 00:34:49,070
He didn't show up.

523
00:34:49,071 --> 00:34:51,781
Fischer lost the opening match
to Spassky last night...

524
00:34:51,782 --> 00:34:54,492
...after walking out during the match
for 30 minutes...

525
00:34:54,493 --> 00:34:57,912
...to protest the directions and distractions
of television cameras...

526
00:34:57,913 --> 00:34:59,538
...which were later withdrawn.

527
00:34:59,539 --> 00:35:02,124
On Wall Street,
prices took a pounding yesterday...

528
00:35:02,125 --> 00:35:05,753
...with the Dow Jones closing down
6-and-three-quarter points.

529
00:35:05,754 --> 00:35:08,589
The dollar took a beating
on the European money market...

530
00:35:08,590 --> 00:35:10,385
...dropping to its lower....

531
00:35:51,633 --> 00:35:54,146
Taxi. Taxi.

532
00:36:06,314 --> 00:36:09,443
Taxi. Taxi.

533
00:36:20,996 --> 00:36:22,944
Taxi.

534
00:37:58,844 --> 00:38:01,679
- Where are you?
- Stuck.

535
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:04,860
The story has stalled on us.

536
00:38:06,685 --> 00:38:09,556
And you thought I'd help?

537
00:38:11,731 --> 00:38:14,244
I'll never quote you.

538
00:38:15,485 --> 00:38:17,987
I wouldn't quote you
even as an anonymous source.

539
00:38:17,988 --> 00:38:21,577
I mean, you'd be on deep background.

540
00:38:23,952 --> 00:38:25,845
You can trust me. You know that.

541
00:38:29,291 --> 00:38:31,084
Go on.

542
00:38:33,295 --> 00:38:38,095
- Can you tell me what you know?
- You tell me what you know.

543
00:38:41,636 --> 00:38:45,175
Hunt worked for Colson
at the White House.

544
00:38:45,348 --> 00:38:48,392
Hunt was investigating Kennedy
at Chappaquiddick.

545
00:38:48,393 --> 00:38:53,193
That should tell you a lot. What else?

546
00:38:53,315 --> 00:38:57,735
We're beginning to hear a lot about a lawyer
at CREEP named Gordon Liddy who's...

547
00:39:12,667 --> 00:39:14,793
Gordon Liddy...

548
00:39:14,794 --> 00:39:19,173
...was fired by Mitchell
because he wouldn't talk to the FBI.

549
00:39:19,174 --> 00:39:22,866
- You'll hear more.
- Will he talk?

550
00:39:27,515 --> 00:39:28,849
I was at a party once...

551
00:39:28,850 --> 00:39:33,650
...and Liddy put his hand over a candle,
and he kept it there.

552
00:39:34,147 --> 00:39:38,947
He kept it right in the flame
until his flesh was burned.

553
00:39:39,694 --> 00:39:44,494
Somebody said, "What's the trick?"
And Liddy said, "The trick is not minding."

554
00:39:48,203 --> 00:39:50,920
The story is dry.

555
00:39:51,665 --> 00:39:54,041
All we've got are pieces.

556
00:39:54,042 --> 00:39:58,045
We can't seem to figure out
what the puzzle is supposed to look like.

557
00:39:58,046 --> 00:40:00,714
John Mitchell resigns
as the head of CREEP...

558
00:40:00,715 --> 00:40:03,425
...and says he wants
to spend more time with his family.

559
00:40:03,426 --> 00:40:06,220
That sounds like bullshit.
We don't exactly believe that.

560
00:40:06,221 --> 00:40:09,401
No, but it's touching.

561
00:40:11,309 --> 00:40:16,109
Forget the myths that the media has created
about the White House.

562
00:40:16,231 --> 00:40:18,983
The truth is,
these are not very bright guys...

563
00:40:18,984 --> 00:40:21,547
...and things got out of hand.

564
00:40:22,529 --> 00:40:25,447
Hunt's come in from the cold.

565
00:40:25,448 --> 00:40:30,035
Supposedly, he's got a lawyer
with $25,000 in a brown paper bag.

566
00:40:30,036 --> 00:40:32,343
Follow the money.

567
00:40:34,124 --> 00:40:36,123
What do you mean?

568
00:40:36,626 --> 00:40:39,241
- Where?
- Oh, I can't tell you that.

569
00:40:39,587 --> 00:40:41,587
But you could tell me, then.

570
00:40:42,257 --> 00:40:44,883
No, I have to do this my way.

571
00:40:44,884 --> 00:40:48,554
You tell me what you know,
and I'll confirm.

572
00:40:48,555 --> 00:40:53,355
I'll keep you in the right direction if I can,
but that's all.

573
00:40:55,812 --> 00:40:59,504
Just follow the money.

574
00:41:08,783 --> 00:41:12,835
- Goddamn New York Times.
- What is it?

575
00:41:13,288 --> 00:41:18,088
Phone calls from the burglars
in Miami to the Committee to Reelect.

576
00:41:20,670 --> 00:41:22,296
Fifteen phone calls.

577
00:41:22,297 --> 00:41:25,174
At least 15 phone calls,
and those phone calls were made...

578
00:41:25,175 --> 00:41:28,135
...as early as March 15th,
three months before the break-in.

579
00:41:28,136 --> 00:41:31,972
"Eighty-nine thousand dollars issued in
the name of a prominent Mexican lawyer."

580
00:41:31,973 --> 00:41:34,933
Eighty-nine thousand dollars
in Mexican checks?

581
00:41:34,934 --> 00:41:37,345
Why didn't we get this?

582
00:41:37,812 --> 00:41:39,021
Who are their sources?

583
00:41:39,022 --> 00:41:42,561
I even know someone
who works on the phone company.

584
00:41:42,984 --> 00:41:45,486
Carl, if John Mitchell
wanted your phone records...

585
00:41:45,487 --> 00:41:47,613
...you'd be yelling invasion of privacy.

586
00:41:47,614 --> 00:41:49,656
Was the New York Times article accurate?

587
00:41:49,657 --> 00:41:52,326
- Yeah, but I can't get you a fuller listing.
- Why?

588
00:41:52,327 --> 00:41:54,787
They've subpoenaed
all of Barker's phone records.

589
00:41:54,788 --> 00:41:59,588
I think they're trying to find out if the
Watergate burglars broke any Florida law.

590
00:42:00,418 --> 00:42:02,586
- Who subpoenaed them?
- Miami DA.

591
00:42:02,587 --> 00:42:04,755
- What's his name?
- I don't know his name.

592
00:42:04,756 --> 00:42:07,674
But the guy who's heading the investigation
is named Dardis.

593
00:42:07,675 --> 00:42:10,260
Dardis. What's his first name?

594
00:42:10,261 --> 00:42:14,264
I don't know his first name.
I guess you'll have to find that out.

595
00:42:21,022 --> 00:42:22,231
- Hi.
- Hello.

596
00:42:22,232 --> 00:42:24,525
I have a 9:15 appointment
with Mr. Dardis.

597
00:42:24,526 --> 00:42:28,403
Mr. Bernstein, I'm afraid that Mr. Dardis
won't be able to see you this morning.

598
00:42:28,404 --> 00:42:31,073
- His calendar is quite full.
- There must be a mistake.

599
00:42:31,074 --> 00:42:33,200
I made the appointment
with him personally.

600
00:42:33,201 --> 00:42:35,536
The appointment should've been made
through me.

601
00:42:35,537 --> 00:42:37,746
I'll see if I can squeeze you in later.

602
00:42:37,747 --> 00:42:40,260
Oh, thanks very much.

603
00:42:40,834 --> 00:42:45,170
I guess it's difficult
when he makes his own appointments.

604
00:42:45,171 --> 00:42:48,710
Yes, well, we try to handle it.

605
00:42:55,890 --> 00:42:59,560
It's 4:00. We'll be back
in 15 minutes. Do you want anything?

606
00:42:59,561 --> 00:43:03,150
- Coffee, black.
- Coffee, black.

607
00:43:07,110 --> 00:43:08,902
I'm still here.

608
00:43:08,903 --> 00:43:10,612
Ha, ha. I'm so glad.

609
00:43:10,613 --> 00:43:13,490
If you could get me in for five minutes,
I'd appreciate it.

610
00:43:13,491 --> 00:43:16,535
- Mr. Bernstein.
- I have to get back.

611
00:43:16,536 --> 00:43:19,099
We're going to try.

612
00:43:21,082 --> 00:43:24,159
Oh, hi. He's expecting you.

613
00:43:28,756 --> 00:43:30,424
I do have a couple things to do.

614
00:43:30,425 --> 00:43:33,177
I'll be at the Sheraton
if you wanna reach me.

615
00:43:33,178 --> 00:43:36,430
If he has space tomorrow, I'd appreciate it.
Number's on the back.

616
00:43:36,431 --> 00:43:38,432
- Fine.
- I thank you for your patience.

617
00:43:38,433 --> 00:43:42,644
Mm-hm. Thank you, Mr. Bernstein.
Tomorrow it should be better.

618
00:43:42,645 --> 00:43:45,106
I guess so.

619
00:43:48,610 --> 00:43:49,818
Mr. Dardis' office.

620
00:43:49,819 --> 00:43:53,572
Hi. Please tell Mr. Dardis
that Mr. Bernstein has just left.

621
00:43:53,573 --> 00:43:55,908
He'll be available all day tomorrow.

622
00:43:55,909 --> 00:43:58,869
I think we can probably squeeze him in
around 4:30.

623
00:43:58,870 --> 00:44:00,078
- Yes.
- Mm-hm.

624
00:44:00,079 --> 00:44:04,041
And please tell Mr. Dardis he doesn't want
to be late for his 6:30 appointment.

625
00:44:04,042 --> 00:44:07,118
- Yes, I will.
- Mm-hm. Thank you.

626
00:44:14,052 --> 00:44:16,929
- Mr. Dardis' office.
- Mr. Martinson at the county clerk's.

627
00:44:16,930 --> 00:44:19,431
- Beg your pardon?
- Martinson at the county clerk's.

628
00:44:19,432 --> 00:44:23,477
There's some records that Dardis wanted.
Could you come get them? We're closing.

629
00:44:23,478 --> 00:44:26,554
Uh, well, yes, I'll be right over.

630
00:44:31,527 --> 00:44:33,527
Excuse me.

631
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,673
Would be easier too, wouldn't it?

632
00:44:52,674 --> 00:44:55,801
All right. Hold it. What?

633
00:44:55,802 --> 00:44:57,803
- Excuse me.
- Can I help you in some way?

634
00:44:57,804 --> 00:44:59,972
I'm Carl Bernstein. I've been here since 9.

635
00:44:59,973 --> 00:45:02,557
- Wait outside.
- I've been waiting since this morning.

636
00:45:02,558 --> 00:45:05,060
- Finish your call.
- Wait outside, please, will you?

637
00:45:05,061 --> 00:45:07,354
No, no, no.
I'm the reporter from the Post.

638
00:45:07,355 --> 00:45:09,064
We talked on the phone yesterday.

639
00:45:09,065 --> 00:45:12,192
- You told me to come here, and I'm here.
- Okay, yeah, look...

640
00:45:12,193 --> 00:45:14,987
I've got the press here.
I'm gonna have to call you back.

641
00:45:14,988 --> 00:45:18,073
If you didn't wanna see me,
I don't know why you didn't tell me.

642
00:45:18,074 --> 00:45:21,118
I wasted a whole day here,
and my paper's waiting for a story.

643
00:45:21,119 --> 00:45:23,829
You tell me to come,
you said I got a 9:30 appointment.

644
00:45:23,830 --> 00:45:27,291
- I've been waiting the whole day.
- Caught me on the worst day possible.

645
00:45:27,292 --> 00:45:29,876
The man I work for
has started a reelection campaign.

646
00:45:29,877 --> 00:45:32,212
We're gonna have to
see each other tomorrow.

647
00:45:32,213 --> 00:45:35,048
No, I'm facing a deadline.
My paper's saving space for me.

648
00:45:35,049 --> 00:45:38,510
- I just don't have a minute now.
- Well, I'm sorry, but...

649
00:45:38,511 --> 00:45:41,471
Uh, Mr. Dardis, I'm really
very sorry about this. Mr. Bernstein...

650
00:45:41,472 --> 00:45:44,975
I beg your pardon, but this gentleman
made the appointment with me...

651
00:45:44,976 --> 00:45:47,728
...and the Washington Post
deserves the same courtesy...

652
00:45:47,729 --> 00:45:49,479
...as any of the people waiting.

653
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:53,070
I'll buzz you in about five minutes.

654
00:45:54,068 --> 00:45:56,786
The lady takes good care of me.

655
00:45:57,071 --> 00:45:59,948
The fact is we just can't go into it
this evening.

656
00:45:59,949 --> 00:46:02,034
It's gonna have to wait until tomorrow.

657
00:46:02,035 --> 00:46:04,202
I wish you could've told me
before I left...

658
00:46:04,203 --> 00:46:09,003
...because I gotta go back to my paper now
and write that story one way or another.

659
00:46:11,586 --> 00:46:15,756
You wanna see Mr. Barker's phone records
and his money records?

660
00:46:15,757 --> 00:46:18,425
You told me you'd show me
everything you got on Barker.

661
00:46:18,426 --> 00:46:19,676
That's all I want.

662
00:46:19,677 --> 00:46:23,055
- Well, that's what I've got.
- Well, that's fine.

663
00:46:23,056 --> 00:46:25,182
You and I have to have an agreement...

664
00:46:25,183 --> 00:46:29,061
...that you're not gonna reveal the source
of your information.

665
00:46:29,062 --> 00:46:33,440
All these are cashier's checks
on a bank in Mexico City.

666
00:46:33,441 --> 00:46:35,442
- All these checks from Mexico?
- You see?

667
00:46:35,443 --> 00:46:37,569
How come?
Did the money originate there?

668
00:46:37,570 --> 00:46:39,946
Well, I doubt it started off as pesos.

669
00:46:39,947 --> 00:46:41,656
Uh....

670
00:46:41,657 --> 00:46:45,035
- Well, wait a minute, what's this one?
- Uh, what's...? Okay, $25,000.

671
00:46:45,036 --> 00:46:47,954
- Who's that? Who is that? Dahl...?
- Kenneth H. Dahlberg.

672
00:46:47,955 --> 00:46:50,207
We haven't been able to ascertain
who that is.

673
00:46:50,208 --> 00:46:52,626
Bob, I've got something.
I don't know what it is.

674
00:46:52,627 --> 00:46:54,795
Somewhere,
there is a Kenneth H. Dahlberg.

675
00:46:54,796 --> 00:46:57,339
We gotta get to him
before the New York Times does.

676
00:46:57,340 --> 00:47:00,759
I think they have the same information.
Got a pencil? Write this down.

677
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:05,560
Kenneth H. Dahlberg.
D-A-H-L-B-E-R-G, Dahlberg.

678
00:47:05,807 --> 00:47:09,226
McGovern, who at first
voiced complete support for Eagleton...

679
00:47:09,227 --> 00:47:13,063
...has more recently expressed doubts
and said Eagleton must make a decision...

680
00:47:13,064 --> 00:47:15,315
...whether to stay or leave the ticket.

681
00:47:15,316 --> 00:47:17,025
More with Jean Westwood....

682
00:47:17,026 --> 00:47:20,112
You're the one that wanted
the articles on Kenneth H. Dahlberg?

683
00:47:20,113 --> 00:47:22,823
- Yeah.
- Couldn't find anything in the clip file at all.

684
00:47:22,824 --> 00:47:24,825
- Oh, wonderful.
- Um....

685
00:47:24,826 --> 00:47:29,391
I did find one picture though,
if it's any help.

686
00:47:30,415 --> 00:47:32,260
- Thanks.
- Mm.

687
00:47:37,296 --> 00:47:39,131
Minnesota.

688
00:47:39,132 --> 00:47:41,299
...supported Senator Eagleman.

689
00:47:41,300 --> 00:47:44,845
He is an able United States senator....

690
00:47:44,846 --> 00:47:46,179
Minneapolis, Minneapolis.

691
00:47:46,180 --> 00:47:50,392
...will make him a prominent figure
in American politics...

692
00:47:50,393 --> 00:47:53,213
...for many, many years.

693
00:48:02,196 --> 00:48:06,996
I base that conclusion
upon my conversations with his doctors...

694
00:48:07,952 --> 00:48:11,580
...and my close personal
and political association with him.

695
00:48:11,581 --> 00:48:13,874
- Outside line, please.
- Yes.

696
00:48:13,875 --> 00:48:15,750
- Thank you.
- In the joint decision...

697
00:48:15,751 --> 00:48:20,380
...that we have reached tonight,
health was not a factor.

698
00:48:20,381 --> 00:48:25,181
But the public debate over
Senator Eagleman's past medical history...

699
00:48:26,179 --> 00:48:30,599
...continues to divert attention
from the great national issues...

700
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:33,143
...that need to be discussed.

701
00:48:33,144 --> 00:48:37,944
I have referred to the growing pressures
to ask for Senator Eagleton's withdrawal.

702
00:48:39,734 --> 00:48:42,694
- We have also seen....
- Hello?

703
00:48:42,695 --> 00:48:44,696
- Could I please...? Mr. Dahlberg?
- Yes?

704
00:48:44,697 --> 00:48:47,449
- Kenneth Dahlberg?
- Yes?

705
00:48:47,450 --> 00:48:51,502
This is Bob Woodward
of the Washington Post.

706
00:48:51,579 --> 00:48:53,914
- Yes?
- About that $25,000 check...

707
00:48:53,915 --> 00:48:57,250
...deposited in the bank account
