Well, we're after a list
of CREEP employees.

937
01:00:43,290 --> 01:00:45,666
- Where is it?
- It's classified.

938
01:00:45,667 --> 01:00:49,295
- Well, how you gonna get it?
- We haven't had any luck yet.

939
01:00:49,296 --> 01:00:51,141
Get some.

940
01:00:55,844 --> 01:00:57,433
Anything else?

941
01:01:07,272 --> 01:01:09,939
You made a mistake in there.

942
01:01:12,819 --> 01:01:14,362
What?

943
01:01:14,363 --> 01:01:17,740
You said we haven't had any luck yet,
that's the thing he jumps on.

944
01:01:17,741 --> 01:01:19,116
You can't talk about luck.

945
01:01:19,117 --> 01:01:22,656
If you can't talk in specifics,
you shouldn't say anything.

946
01:01:28,001 --> 01:01:30,127
Is there any place you don't smoke?

947
01:01:32,881 --> 01:01:34,674
- What?
- Hold it. Hold it.

948
01:01:34,675 --> 01:01:36,968
- What are you doing?
- Kay Eddy.

949
01:01:36,969 --> 01:01:40,263
Doesn't she go with a guy
that works for the Committee to Reelect?

950
01:01:40,264 --> 01:01:41,847
- Meet me at 4.
- All right.

951
01:01:41,848 --> 01:01:43,474
- Eddy? Hey.
- Just a second.

952
01:01:43,475 --> 01:01:46,811
- Kay, can...?
- 757-6521.

953
01:01:46,812 --> 01:01:49,772
Okay, I'll get back to you on this.
Thanks.

954
01:01:49,773 --> 01:01:54,184
Don't you go with a guy that works
for the Committee to Reelect?

955
01:01:54,236 --> 01:01:56,362
- Not anymore.
- You did go with him, though.

956
01:01:56,363 --> 01:01:59,156
- You were engaged to him, weren't you?
- Yeah.

957
01:01:59,157 --> 01:02:01,464
You got out of it?

958
01:02:01,702 --> 01:02:04,036
- So?
- You're looking better.

959
01:02:06,957 --> 01:02:09,208
We need a list of the people
that work there.

960
01:02:09,209 --> 01:02:10,876
Do you think that...?

961
01:02:10,877 --> 01:02:13,963
- I can't do that.
- Why not?

962
01:02:13,964 --> 01:02:15,214
That's personal.

963
01:02:15,215 --> 01:02:18,446
What do you mean? You said it was over.

964
01:02:20,554 --> 01:02:23,180
You're asking me
to use a guy I care about.

965
01:02:23,181 --> 01:02:26,017
No, no, we're not asking you
to use him, just to help us.

966
01:02:26,018 --> 01:02:28,561
- Well, sure you...
- I mean, we'd do the same for you.

967
01:02:28,562 --> 01:02:30,896
My only chance of getting that
is if I see him.

968
01:02:30,897 --> 01:02:33,858
- I don't wanna see him again.
- Well, do you have to see him?

969
01:02:33,859 --> 01:02:36,360
- Sure, I have to.
- Do you have to see him that way?

970
01:02:36,361 --> 01:02:37,862
Can't you just call him up...

971
01:02:37,863 --> 01:02:40,906
...and say you wanna have a drink with him,
just feel him out?

972
01:02:40,907 --> 01:02:45,342
You say the relationship is over.
I mean, what the hell do you have to lose?

973
01:02:45,454 --> 01:02:47,453
Forget it.

974
01:02:47,539 --> 01:02:49,749
Don't do anything
that would embarrass you...

975
01:02:49,750 --> 01:02:52,724
...or that you don't feel right about.

976
01:02:53,003 --> 01:02:55,002
Forget it.

977
01:02:55,589 --> 01:02:57,434
Let's go.

978
01:03:03,180 --> 01:03:06,265
Don't let her get off like that.
She was gonna say something.

979
01:03:06,266 --> 01:03:07,600
You're overdramatizing.

980
01:03:07,601 --> 01:03:10,144
- She was gonna give us what we wanted.
- It was over.

981
01:03:10,145 --> 01:03:12,247
- What?
- It was over.

982
01:03:16,943 --> 01:03:19,904
This looks like your story.
Why don't you take a look at it?

983
01:03:19,905 --> 01:03:22,417
I'm gonna check this out.

984
01:03:25,786 --> 01:03:29,478
You're gonna get fat
eating all those doughnuts.

985
01:03:56,483 --> 01:03:59,151
- Is this the whole list?
- Look what it says.

986
01:03:59,152 --> 01:04:03,255
"Personnel,
Committee to Reelect the President."

987
01:04:03,532 --> 01:04:04,740
This is alphabetical.

988
01:04:04,741 --> 01:04:07,785
You can't tell who works for who.

989
01:04:07,786 --> 01:04:09,578
Mitchell, Magruder, Stans.

990
01:04:09,579 --> 01:04:10,996
Here. John Mitchell.

991
01:04:10,997 --> 01:04:12,331
- What's the number?
- 301.

992
01:04:12,332 --> 01:04:15,501
All right, find somebody
who has a number close to it.

993
01:04:15,502 --> 01:04:18,696
- They probably work for him. Okay.
- Here's a 303.

994
01:04:20,757 --> 01:04:24,218
Okay, we have to find out how
the money got from Stans to the burglars.

995
01:04:24,219 --> 01:04:27,012
Somebody who worked in Finance.

996
01:04:27,013 --> 01:04:30,015
All right, here's the head of Finance.
Maurice Stans, 269.

997
01:04:30,016 --> 01:04:33,978
If we can just get somebody
who works under Stans.

998
01:04:33,979 --> 01:04:36,021
- Uh, Sloan? You need him?
- He's the treasurer.

999
01:04:36,022 --> 01:04:38,107
- What's the number?
- It's Hugh Sloan, 287.

1000
01:04:38,108 --> 01:04:40,158
Is there a secretary?

1001
01:04:41,153 --> 01:04:44,530
- Wait a minute. Manley, Manley, Manley.
- Here it is. Irene Manley?

1002
01:04:44,531 --> 01:04:48,242
- Yeah.
- 1406 Lee Jackson Memorial Highway.

1003
01:04:48,243 --> 01:04:50,369
- Hi, I'm Bob Woodward.
- I'm Carl Bernstein.

1004
01:04:50,370 --> 01:04:53,497
We're from the Washington Post.
We'd like to speak to you.

1005
01:04:53,498 --> 01:04:56,542
We understand your daughter works
for the Committee to Reelect.

1006
01:04:56,543 --> 01:04:59,670
- Wouldn't be anything embarrassing.
- Would you object to just...?

1007
01:04:59,671 --> 01:05:01,260
Forget it.

1008
01:05:01,965 --> 01:05:03,174
Yes? Hi. CARL: Hi.

1009
01:05:03,175 --> 01:05:04,717
- Miss Milland? Betty Milland?
- Mm-hm.

1010
01:05:04,718 --> 01:05:06,677
- I'm Bob Woodward.
- Carl Bernstein.

1011
01:05:06,678 --> 01:05:08,304
We're from the Washington Post.

1012
01:05:08,305 --> 01:05:11,485
I know you're trying to do your job.
I mean....

1013
01:05:11,600 --> 01:05:13,893
You don't understand
the pressure we're under.

1014
01:05:13,894 --> 01:05:17,062
- If we could come in for a couple seconds...
- No, I really don't...

1015
01:05:17,063 --> 01:05:18,272
We don't wanna come in.

1016
01:05:18,273 --> 01:05:22,443
We understand there was some documents
that were shredded at the committee.

1017
01:05:22,444 --> 01:05:24,195
Well, there, uh....

1018
01:05:24,196 --> 01:05:26,655
There's often shredding.
I mean, we do that a lot.

1019
01:05:26,656 --> 01:05:28,532
Were you there during the shredding?

1020
01:05:28,533 --> 01:05:29,950
- Yes, I was.
- I see.

1021
01:05:29,951 --> 01:05:33,621
Were there any department heads
from the committee who were also present?

1022
01:05:33,622 --> 01:05:36,665
Uh, yes. Mr. Mitchell came in one night.

1023
01:05:36,666 --> 01:05:37,875
- John Mitchell?
- Yes.

1024
01:05:37,876 --> 01:05:39,251
- The attorney general?
- Uh-huh.

1025
01:05:39,252 --> 01:05:42,087
He was carrying a raincoat over his head.

1026
01:05:42,088 --> 01:05:44,089
You know, because he was...
I thought he was gonna go:

1027
01:05:44,090 --> 01:05:45,549
Woo-hoo. Woo-hoo.

1028
01:05:45,550 --> 01:05:48,177
- But, uh, I...
- Did he supervise the shredding?

1029
01:05:48,178 --> 01:05:50,429
Uh, I just...
Can I not answer any more questions?

1030
01:05:50,430 --> 01:05:53,516
I'd just as soon not....
Okay? Maybe I could call you.

1031
01:05:53,517 --> 01:05:56,901
- It's...
- Are you being told not to talk?

1032
01:05:57,020 --> 01:06:00,689
- Will you call us?
- I don't know.

1033
01:06:00,690 --> 01:06:02,024
I'll try.

1034
01:06:02,025 --> 01:06:04,527
What about that shredding
right after the break-in?

1035
01:06:04,528 --> 01:06:06,695
We need to know the papers
in the shredding.

1036
01:06:06,696 --> 01:06:10,449
You have some idea what's in the papers
when the attorney general comes in...

1037
01:06:10,450 --> 01:06:13,577
...it's at the committee,
and he's got a raincoat over his head.

1038
01:06:13,578 --> 01:06:16,413
It could be raining.
Let me go through the story again.

1039
01:06:16,414 --> 01:06:18,832
You got a woman who's frightened.
Works for CREEP.

1040
01:06:18,833 --> 01:06:21,961
She said there's shredding.
We don't know what's in the papers.

1041
01:06:21,962 --> 01:06:25,631
We know the former attorney general
comes in with an overcoat over his head.

1042
01:06:25,632 --> 01:06:29,385
Could be raining. There's a lawyer present.
We don't know what he asked them.

1043
01:06:29,386 --> 01:06:31,387
Will you tell me where there's a story?

1044
01:06:31,388 --> 01:06:34,557
In the fact that the interview
did not take place in her home...

1045
01:06:34,558 --> 01:06:36,475
...but in the office of the committee.

1046
01:06:36,476 --> 01:06:40,312
- How is there a story in that?
- Because there's a lawyer in the office.

1047
01:06:40,313 --> 01:06:42,773
- You're more resistant than she is.
- That's right.

1048
01:06:42,774 --> 01:06:45,442
- Why?
- Because there's not enough fact.

1049
01:06:45,443 --> 01:06:49,819
Well, then let's just turn around
and go back and question her again.

1050
01:06:50,615 --> 01:06:53,659
- This won't take long at all. We just...
- Please go away, okay?

1051
01:06:53,660 --> 01:06:56,579
Will you please leave
before they see you?

1052
01:06:56,580 --> 01:06:59,707
- Who did you mean by...?
- What do you mean, "they"?

1053
01:06:59,708 --> 01:07:01,458
Could you give us their names?

1054
01:07:01,459 --> 01:07:05,879
We haven't revealed the sources
of the people that have talked to us.

1055
01:07:05,880 --> 01:07:10,680
- I really can't talk about this because...
- Would they be members of the committee?

1056
01:07:13,179 --> 01:07:15,180
Someone got to that woman.

1057
01:07:15,181 --> 01:07:16,974
It's the key to the whole cover-up.

1058
01:07:16,975 --> 01:07:20,185
How can you write there's a cover-up?
We don't know that there is.

1059
01:07:20,186 --> 01:07:24,986
Then I don't know what the hell you need.
So you tell me what you need.

1060
01:07:25,066 --> 01:07:28,360
I need more fact for a story,
and I think you should need the same.

1061
01:07:28,361 --> 01:07:31,030
- If you get in a car and there's music...
- I'm in a car.

1062
01:07:31,031 --> 01:07:33,490
There's music playing in the car...
Hypothetically.

1063
01:07:33,491 --> 01:07:36,535
There's music playing for 10 minutes
and there's no commercial.

1064
01:07:36,536 --> 01:07:38,120
What can you deduce from that?

1065
01:07:38,121 --> 01:07:39,455
- Is it AM or FM?
- Come on.

1066
01:07:39,456 --> 01:07:40,706
Is it AM or FM?

1067
01:07:40,707 --> 01:07:44,918
A guy can come up to me on the street,
and he can ask me an address.

1068
01:07:44,919 --> 01:07:47,880
Now, is the man interrogating me,
or is he lost?

1069
01:07:47,881 --> 01:07:49,548
What kind of a story do I write?

1070
01:07:49,549 --> 01:07:51,759
What kind of a deduction
do I make from that?

1071
01:07:51,760 --> 01:07:54,928
You don't have a gut feeling
that the woman is trying to help us?

1072
01:07:54,929 --> 01:07:58,160
I don't have enough gut feeling.
I wish I did.

1073
01:07:58,558 --> 01:08:01,635
We're from the Washington Post.

1074
01:08:02,312 --> 01:08:04,500
Ammons, Irene Ammons. Did we see her?

1075
01:08:05,231 --> 01:08:10,031
Abbott, Addison, Augusto, Alberts.

1076
01:08:16,785 --> 01:08:19,453
Is there something that strikes you
as odd about this?

1077
01:08:19,454 --> 01:08:21,372
- What?
- It's like there's a pattern...

1078
01:08:21,373 --> 01:08:24,667
...to the way they're not talking,
the way they say no all the time.

1079
01:08:24,668 --> 01:08:26,154
I think it's odd.

1080
01:08:26,252 --> 01:08:27,961
- Mrs. Hambling?
- Yes.

1081
01:08:27,962 --> 01:08:32,716
- Hi, we're from the Washington Post.
- I'm Carl Bernstein, this is Bob Woodward.

1082
01:08:32,717 --> 01:08:35,761
A friend of the committee
said that we could contact you.

1083
01:08:35,762 --> 01:08:37,971
- Who was it?
- We can't reveal that.

1084
01:08:37,972 --> 01:08:40,432
You can talk to us.
We don't reveal our sources.

1085
01:08:40,433 --> 01:08:42,935
You people.

1086
01:08:42,936 --> 01:08:46,897
You think you can come into my home,
ask a few questions...

1087
01:08:46,898 --> 01:08:51,698
...have me destroy the reputations
of men that I work for and respect?

1088
01:08:53,071 --> 01:08:55,447
Do you understand loyalty?

1089
01:08:55,448 --> 01:08:58,525
Have you ever heard of loyalty?

1090
01:08:58,576 --> 01:09:00,369
- Hi.
- Yes?

1091
01:09:00,370 --> 01:09:02,121
- I'm Bob Woodward.
- Carl Bernstein.

1092
01:09:02,122 --> 01:09:04,707
- We're from the Washington Post.
- Yes.

1093
01:09:04,708 --> 01:09:08,460
I've read what you've written.
I wanna thank you.

1094
01:09:08,461 --> 01:09:11,964
I've been a Republican all my life,
but this goes beyond party politics.

1095
01:09:11,965 --> 01:09:14,591
Would you mind
if we asked you a few questions?

1096
01:09:14,592 --> 01:09:17,259
No, no. Come in. Would you like coffee?

1097
01:09:18,096 --> 01:09:19,680
Sure.

1098
01:09:19,681 --> 01:09:22,599
What they've done
is a threat to the Constitution.

1099
01:09:22,600 --> 01:09:24,893
It goes against everything we stand for.

1100
01:09:24,894 --> 01:09:28,063
Could you be a little bit more specific
than that?

1101
01:09:28,064 --> 01:09:30,858
I'm afraid your articles
have just scratched the surface.

1102
01:09:30,859 --> 01:09:33,652
You don't mind
if I just take a few notes, do you?

1103
01:09:33,653 --> 01:09:35,448
No.

1104
01:09:35,822 --> 01:09:38,532
How long have you worked
at the committee?

1105
01:09:38,533 --> 01:09:39,742
Committee?

1106
01:09:39,743 --> 01:09:44,204
Yes, the Committee
to Reelect the President.

1107
01:09:44,205 --> 01:09:48,167
Oh. Oh, no, I don't work
at the Committee to Reelect the President.

1108
01:09:48,168 --> 01:09:52,968
I work at Garfinckel's,
in the Accounting Department.

1109
01:09:55,800 --> 01:09:59,219
- Miss Abbott?
- Yes.

1110
01:09:59,220 --> 01:10:01,425
Judith Abbott?

1111
01:10:03,099 --> 01:10:06,073
Carolyn Abbott.

1112
01:10:07,645 --> 01:10:10,465
We're just doing something wrong.

1113
01:10:12,692 --> 01:10:15,611
- It's never been there.
- No.

1114
01:10:15,612 --> 01:10:18,227
We're doing something wrong.

1115
01:10:18,364 --> 01:10:20,866
It's just not good enough.

1116
01:10:20,867 --> 01:10:24,369
How can you keep going at something
past the point when you'd believe it?

1117
01:10:24,370 --> 01:10:26,831
Just have to start all over again.

1118
01:10:32,212 --> 01:10:35,172
Nasemith, Narrow, Ness...

1119
01:10:35,173 --> 01:10:37,508
...Nickels, Nixon...

1120
01:10:37,509 --> 01:10:39,551
Ed Nixon.

1121
01:10:39,552 --> 01:10:42,638
Jolson, Jones...

1122
01:10:42,639 --> 01:10:44,807
...Jordan, Jost.

1123
01:10:44,808 --> 01:10:48,227
If we could only get somebody
that worked for Finance to talk.

1124
01:10:48,228 --> 01:10:50,145
- What about the bookkeeper?
- Which?

1125
01:10:50,146 --> 01:10:52,439
The bookkeeper that worked
for both Slans and...

1126
01:10:52,440 --> 01:10:54,441
- Oh, you're all right.
- Sloan and Stans.

1127
01:10:54,442 --> 01:10:57,402
I've been there. I've called her twice.
There's no answer.

1128
01:10:57,403 --> 01:11:00,113
I say we should start again.

1129
01:11:00,114 --> 01:11:04,409
Abbott, Addison, Augusto, Alberts...

1130
01:11:04,410 --> 01:11:07,329
...Aldus, Alessandro....

1131
01:11:07,330 --> 01:11:10,916
Eulosky, Clan, Constell....

1132
01:11:10,917 --> 01:11:15,212
Boyle, Brenner, Bromley, Jost....

1133
01:11:15,213 --> 01:11:19,508
Nasemith, Narrow, Ness, Nickels....

1134
01:11:19,509 --> 01:11:23,098
Teeny, Sandstrom....

1135
01:11:23,847 --> 01:11:27,057
Skroes, Skully...

1136
01:11:27,058 --> 01:11:30,135
Skully. We've been there twice.

1137
01:11:30,645 --> 01:11:34,940
All right, Wilcox, Winthrow,
Windsor, Worts....

1138
01:11:34,941 --> 01:11:38,110
Two weeks work, half the names
crossed off and what have you got?

1139
01:11:38,111 --> 01:11:39,862
People aren't talking, Harry.

1140
01:11:39,863 --> 01:11:42,698
And it's the way they're not talking
that's unnatural.

1141
01:11:42,699 --> 01:11:46,118
We've been up all night.
We went over all the quotes of the people...

1142
01:11:46,119 --> 01:11:48,620
It's like they're getting instructions.
It's pat.

1143
01:11:48,621 --> 01:11:51,081
You wanna hear some real news?

1144
01:11:51,082 --> 01:11:53,500
That GAO report
in which you placed so much faith?

1145
01:11:53,501 --> 01:11:56,169
It's been postponed
till after tonight's renomination.

1146
01:11:56,170 --> 01:11:58,797
- What do you mean?
- Hughes got a call from Stans.

1147
01:11:58,798 --> 01:12:01,633
Says he has new information,
not to republish without it.

1148
01:12:01,634 --> 01:12:04,469
They're gonna bury the report
till after the renomination.

1149
01:12:04,470 --> 01:12:06,138
The indictment will be out soon.

1150
01:12:06,139 --> 01:12:10,559
Every indication says the indictment will
stop at the five burglars, Hunt and Liddy.

1151
01:12:10,560 --> 01:12:13,586
And that's the end of your story.

1152
01:12:17,483 --> 01:12:22,283
The vote of all the delegates
has been recorded.

1153
01:12:23,114 --> 01:12:27,832
The vote for Richard Nixon...

1154
01:12:28,244 --> 01:12:32,399
...is 1347.

1155
01:12:32,874 --> 01:12:37,674
The vote for Paul McCloskey is 1.

1156
01:12:39,464 --> 01:12:44,264
And therefore I declare the nominee
of the Republican Party...

1157
01:12:45,094 --> 01:12:48,472
...for president of the United States...

1158
01:12:48,473 --> 01:12:51,099
...President Richard Nixon.

1159
01:12:56,189 --> 01:13:00,989
Four more years!
Four more years! Four more years!

1160
01:13:17,877 --> 01:13:22,677
The president and the future
president of the United States of America.

1161
01:13:24,550 --> 01:13:26,885
Wonderful young faces I see out here.

1162
01:13:26,886 --> 01:13:31,431
Your enthusiasm, your idealism,
your hard work.

1163
01:13:31,432 --> 01:13:34,059
This is your first vote...

1164
01:13:34,060 --> 01:13:37,771
...and years from now,
I just hope you can all look back...

1165
01:13:37,772 --> 01:13:40,816
...and say it was one of your best votes.
Thank you.

1166
01:13:43,111 --> 01:13:47,911
Four more years!
Four more years! Four more years!

1167
01:14:05,758 --> 01:14:08,093
Hi, I'm Carl Bernstein
of the Washington Post.

1168
01:14:08,094 --> 01:14:10,637
I just wanna ask you
a couple of questions.

1169
01:14:10,638 --> 01:14:13,223
Well, you don't want me,
you want my sister.

1170
01:14:13,224 --> 01:14:15,600
It's for you. It's Carl Bernstein.

1171
01:14:15,601 --> 01:14:17,728
He's the guy from the Post. Get rid of him.

1172
01:14:17,729 --> 01:14:20,147
Could I just borrow
one of your cigarettes there?

1173
01:14:20,148 --> 01:14:21,891
Sure.

1174
01:14:22,608 --> 01:14:27,320
- You've really gotta go.
- Sure. Could I just get a match?

1175
01:14:27,321 --> 01:14:28,947
I understand your being afraid.

1176
01:14:28,948 --> 01:14:30,782
There's a lot of people like you...

1177
01:14:30,783 --> 01:14:34,786
...who wanted to tell the truth,
but some people wouldn't listen.

1178
01:14:34,787 --> 01:14:38,290
Certain people have gone back
to the prosecutors and the FBI...

1179
01:14:38,291 --> 01:14:41,367
...to give information
which they were never asked.

1180
01:14:42,754 --> 01:14:46,631
You were Hugh Sloan's bookkeeper when
he worked for Maurice Stans up at Finance.

1181
01:14:46,632 --> 01:14:50,427
We were just wondering
if you were promoted...

1182
01:14:50,428 --> 01:14:53,346
...to work for Mr. Stans
immediately after Mr. Sloan quit...

1183
01:14:53,347 --> 01:14:57,450
...or whether there was some time lapse.

1184
01:14:59,729 --> 01:15:04,140
I never worked for Sloan or Stans.

1185
01:15:04,734 --> 01:15:08,236
Uh, can I get you some coffee
or something?

1186
01:15:08,237 --> 01:15:10,596
Yeah, thanks very much.

1187
01:15:14,285 --> 01:15:16,387
Door sticks.

1188
01:15:18,331 --> 01:15:23,131
Uh, could I just sit down for a second?

1189
01:15:24,879 --> 01:15:28,931
Sure, you can sit down,
but I'm not going to tell you anything.

1190
01:15:29,842 --> 01:15:31,585
Okay.

1191
01:15:52,532 --> 01:15:55,659
I was just curious why you lied just then.

1192
01:15:55,660 --> 01:15:58,381
Have you been threatened
if you tell the truth?

1193
01:15:59,747 --> 01:16:01,593
No.

1194
01:16:02,041 --> 01:16:03,630
Never in so many words.

1195
01:16:04,377 --> 01:16:06,378
- How do you like it?
- Just milk, thanks.

1196
01:16:06,379 --> 01:16:08,130
Okay, I'll just get the milk.

1197
01:16:08,131 --> 01:16:12,134
Um, I saw in the wires
that Mrs. Stans was in the hospital.

1198
01:16:12,135 --> 01:16:13,467
Is she feeling better?

1199
01:16:19,142 --> 01:16:21,893
The GAO,
the General Accounting report...

1200
01:16:21,894 --> 01:16:24,729
...said that there was $350,000...

1201
01:16:24,730 --> 01:16:28,900
...in the safe
of the Committee to Reelect the President.

1202
01:16:28,901 --> 01:16:33,004
Were you aware that it was that kind
of funds from the very beginning?

1203
01:16:37,160 --> 01:16:40,787
A lot of people are watching me.
They know I know a lot.

1204
01:16:40,788 --> 01:16:45,588
- Was it all in $100 bills?
- A lot of it was.

1205
01:16:45,877 --> 01:16:48,587
I thought it was
an all-purpose political fund...

1206
01:16:48,588 --> 01:16:51,798
...you know, for taking fat cats to dinner,
things like that.

1207
01:16:51,799 --> 01:16:54,299
Three hundred and fifty thousand dollars
for dinners?

1208
01:16:56,429 --> 01:16:59,249
How was it paid out?

1209
01:17:02,727 --> 01:17:05,701
Not in one big chunk.

1210
01:17:06,272 --> 01:17:08,356
There was a list of 15 names...

1211
01:17:08,357 --> 01:17:12,068
...and the amount of money
given to each person next to the name.

1212
01:17:12,069 --> 01:17:14,889
What happened to the list?

1213
01:17:15,948 --> 01:17:17,741
It was destroyed.

1214
01:17:17,742 --> 01:17:20,049
It was the only record.

1215
01:17:20,494 --> 01:17:24,247
This... Don't pay any attention to this.
This is just for my memory.

1216
01:17:24,248 --> 01:17:26,196
Hate the....

1217
01:17:26,459 --> 01:17:29,741
I have a very bad memory.

1218
01:17:29,962 --> 01:17:31,671
You won't be quoted by name.

1219
01:17:31,672 --> 01:17:35,050
In fact, we get confirmations
before we print anything.

1220
01:17:35,051 --> 01:17:39,851
I can't be positive that that money
was used for the break-in, you understand?

1221
01:17:39,931 --> 01:17:41,640
Yes, I do.

1222
01:17:41,641 --> 01:17:46,410
- But people sure are worried.
- Which people?

1223
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:55,445
Think you could help me
with the disbursement of money...

1224
01:17:55,446 --> 01:17:58,240
...in terms of the number of people
that were involved?

1225
01:17:58,241 --> 01:18:00,138
How many?

1226
01:18:01,911 --> 01:18:04,579
A group of them. About five.
I don't know their names.

1227
01:18:04,580 --> 01:18:09,145
Would Mr. Sloan know?

1228
01:18:10,836 --> 01:18:12,170
Here you are.

1229
01:18:12,171 --> 01:18:16,971
- Would he have any...?
- I don't wanna say anymore, okay?

1230
01:18:22,932 --> 01:18:27,732
Um, I won't be much longer.

1231
01:18:28,729 --> 01:18:33,529
I wonder if you could just help me
a little bit about the money.

1232
01:18:33,776 --> 01:18:37,161
We hear all kinds of figures.

1233
01:18:39,699 --> 01:18:43,410
- There was so much of it.
- How much is "so much"?

1234
01:18:43,411 --> 01:18:47,956
In one two-day period,
6 million dollars came in.

1235
01:18:47,957 --> 01:18:50,625
- Six.
- Six million, cash.

1236
01:18:50,626 --> 01:18:52,421
Mm-hm.

1237
01:18:52,753 --> 01:18:55,984
- We didn't know where to put it all.
- Heh.

1238
01:18:56,173 --> 01:18:57,590
I thought it was all legal.

1239
01:18:57,591 --> 01:19:00,552
I mean, I guess I did
until after the break-in...

1240
01:19:00,553 --> 01:19:02,846
...when I remembered
Gordon got so much of it.

1241
01:19:02,847 --> 01:19:07,206
- This is Mr. Liddy?
- It's all so rotten.

1242
01:19:07,226 --> 01:19:09,687
It's getting worse.

1243
01:19:09,895 --> 01:19:12,981
And the only one I care about
is Hugh Sloan.

1244
01:19:12,982 --> 01:19:17,569
His wife was going to leave him
if he didn't stand up and do what was right.

1245
01:19:17,570 --> 01:19:19,005
So he quit.

1246
01:19:20,448 --> 01:19:22,447
I was wondering...

1247
01:19:23,868 --> 01:19:28,668
...if Hugh Sloan was being set up now
as a fall guy for John Mitchell.

1248
01:19:29,999 --> 01:19:31,742
What do you think?

1249
01:19:39,300 --> 01:19:44,100
If you guys could get John Mitchell,
that would be beautiful.

1250
01:19:51,228 --> 01:19:52,613
Coffee's cold.

1251
01:19:54,648 --> 01:19:57,109
Is there any evidence...

1252
01:19:57,610 --> 01:20:01,815
...that any of Mr. Mitchell's assistants...

1253
01:20:02,156 --> 01:20:03,643
...were part of this?

1254
01:20:04,075 --> 01:20:08,286
I had all the evidence. It was destroyed.
I don't know who destroyed it.

1255
01:20:08,287 --> 01:20:11,498
- I think Gordon did a lot of shredding.
- Hard evidence?

1256
01:20:11,499 --> 01:20:15,752
Well, I can't say that it would positively
prove that they planned the break-in...

1257
01:20:15,753 --> 01:20:17,962
...but it would come pretty close.

1258
01:20:17,963 --> 01:20:22,763
Can you tell me anything, anything,
about who got the money?

1259
01:20:23,052 --> 01:20:27,852
We have had some help on this
from a couple sources...

1260
01:20:28,808 --> 01:20:32,090
...and this is a way of confirming it.

1261
01:20:34,939 --> 01:20:39,275
I don't want you to feel you're in a position
where you have to disclose names.

1262
01:20:39,276 --> 01:20:42,237
You know, I can just ask you initials...

1263
01:20:42,238 --> 01:20:46,282
...and then that way
you're not divulging any information.

1264
01:20:46,283 --> 01:20:49,786
We have some idea.
Would that be all right?

1265
01:20:54,041 --> 01:20:56,451
Was there an M?

1266
01:20:58,838 --> 01:21:00,888
Can you just nod either way?

1267
01:21:02,258 --> 01:21:04,770
Did it go that high up?

1268
01:21:08,139 --> 01:21:09,984
L? Hm.

1269
01:21:11,434 --> 01:21:13,143
I don't wanna say any more, okay?

1270
01:21:13,144 --> 01:21:16,312
I'm sorry, you said L or...?

1271
01:21:16,313 --> 01:21:20,775
I get confused.
Could we just go back for a second?

1272
01:21:20,776 --> 01:21:23,069
In one six-day period,
over $6 million came in.

1273
01:21:23,070 --> 01:21:25,530
Wouldn't believe what was going on
in that woman.

1274
01:21:25,531 --> 01:21:29,200
Stuff was ready to pour out of her.
I'm pouring down coffee to get it out...

1275
01:21:29,201 --> 01:21:30,660
...before she throws me out.

1276
01:21:30,661 --> 01:21:32,912
- Give me your notes so...
- These are the notes.

1277
01:21:32,913 --> 01:21:35,081
- These?
- I got stuff on napkins, matchbooks.

1278
01:21:35,082 --> 01:21:37,792
I'm writing in the bathroom
while she's getting coffee.

1279
01:21:37,793 --> 01:21:39,127
You're crazy. How am I...?

1280
01:21:39,128 --> 01:21:42,297
You'd be crazy too if you were operating
on 20 cups of coffee.

1281
01:21:42,298 --> 01:21:46,301
- Give me something I can get down.
- I got it. I got it all. Okay. Write.

1282
01:21:46,302 --> 01:21:49,554
- Mitchell was in control.
- Wait a minute.

1283
01:21:49,555 --> 01:21:52,015
- There were men working under Mitchell.
- How many?

1284
01:21:52,016 --> 01:21:55,894
I don't know, but the men under Mitchell
received the money from the slush fund.

1285
01:21:55,895 --> 01:21:59,230
- Do we know how much money?
- Yeah, hundreds of thousands of dollars.

1286
01:21:59,231 --> 01:22:02,150
And these men are the key
to what that money was used for.

1287
01:22:02,151 --> 01:22:03,651
Boy, that woman was paranoid.

1288
01:22:03,652 --> 01:22:06,738
At one point, I suddenly wondered
how high up this thing goes...

1289
01:22:06,739 --> 01:22:08,698
...and her paranoia finally got to me.

1290
01:22:08,699 --> 01:22:12,327
I thought what we had was so hot
that CBS or NBC were gonna take the story.

1291
01:22:12,328 --> 01:22:13,536
You're both paranoid.

1292
01:22:13,537 --> 01:22:16,414
She's afraid of Mitchell,
you're afraid of Walter Cronkite.

1293
01:22:16,415 --> 01:22:19,082
- Can we go back to what she said?
- Yeah.

1294
01:22:20,002 --> 01:22:23,437
Here. L, P and M.

1295
01:22:23,714 --> 01:22:25,256
- What do you mean?
- L, P and M.

1296
01:22:25,257 --> 01:22:27,258
- She'd only give me initials.
- Initials?

1297
01:22:27,259 --> 01:22:30,762
Yeah, the initials of the men
that worked under Mitchell: L, P and M.

1298
01:22:30,763 --> 01:22:32,931
You couldn't get the names?

1299
01:22:34,308 --> 01:22:37,435
If I could've, I would've.
I'm trying to get anything I can.

1300
01:22:37,436 --> 01:22:39,812
She said L, P and M...
That's all she'd give me.

1301
01:22:39,813 --> 01:22:41,940
...are the people
who worked under Mitchell.

1302
01:22:41,941 --> 01:22:44,651
She said something about Mitchell.
She hates him.

1303
01:22:44,652 --> 01:22:46,361
- She said that?
- Here. She said:

1304
01:22:46,362 --> 01:22:49,447
"If you guys could get John Mitchell,
that would be beautiful."

1305
01:22:49,448 --> 01:22:51,115
What are you writing about Sloan?

1306
01:22:51,116 --> 01:22:53,701
- "Sloan was the treasurer."
- His wife did what?

1307
01:22:53,702 --> 01:22:57,622
"His wife is pregnant and made Sloan quit.
He no longer wanted to be part of it."

1308
01:22:57,623 --> 01:22:58,957
We've gotta go see Sloan.

1309
01:22:58,958 --> 01:23:00,833
- Okay, make a note of it.
- All right.

1310
01:23:00,834 --> 01:23:03,336
So, what have we got?
Where's that matchbook? Here.

1311
01:23:03,337 --> 01:23:05,588
- L, P and M.
- Okay, L, P and M.

1312
01:23:05,589 --> 01:23:08,466
- L could be LaRue. It could be Liddy.
- L is Liddy.

1313
01:23:08,467 --> 01:23:10,635
- How do we know that?
- Because she said it.

1314
01:23:10,636 --> 01:23:13,221
Right here, she said,
"At the time of the break-in...

1315
01:23:13,222 --> 01:23:16,266
...there was so much money
that I know Gordon got part of it."

1316
01:23:16,267 --> 01:23:19,227
I said, "You mean Gordon Liddy?"
She said yes. So L is Liddy.

1317
01:23:19,228 --> 01:23:20,979
- Right.
- Okay, that leaves P and M.

1318
01:23:20,980 --> 01:23:23,648
P could be Parkinson.

1319
01:23:23,649 --> 01:23:26,317
It could be Porter. It could be...

1320
01:23:26,318 --> 01:23:29,779
Wait a minute. There was a guy.
There was a guy we talked to last week.

1321
01:23:29,780 --> 01:23:33,283
Didn't he say there was a Bart Porter
who was a member of the committee?

1322
01:23:33,284 --> 01:23:37,036
- Porter was called before the grand jury.
- So P is definitely Porter.

1323
01:23:37,037 --> 01:23:38,496
P could be Porter.

1324
01:23:38,497 --> 01:23:42,000
P is Porter, L is Liddy. That leaves....
All that leaves is M.

1325
01:23:42,001 --> 01:23:44,794
M could be McCord. That's out.

1326
01:23:44,795 --> 01:23:47,755
It could be Mardian.

1327
01:23:47,756 --> 01:23:49,757
It could be...

1328
01:23:49,758 --> 01:23:51,634
- ...Magruder.
- I think it's Magruder.

1329
01:23:51,635 --> 01:23:54,470
- I think it's Magruder too.
- Why do you think it is?

1330
01:23:54,471 --> 01:23:57,015
He was second in command under Mitchell.
Why do you?

1331
01:23:57,016 --> 01:24:01,144
Because at one time, he was the temporary
head of the committee, before Mitchell.

1332
01:24:01,145 --> 01:24:05,148
I don't want a cookie. We've gotta get
that bookkeeper to say it was Magruder.

1333
01:24:05,149 --> 01:24:09,152
- Never get her to say anything but "M."
- We gotta go back and get her to say it.

1334
01:24:09,153 --> 01:24:12,405
If we can make names of the initials...

1335
01:24:12,406 --> 01:24:14,991
...we'll know the people
who paid off the burglars.

1336
01:24:14,992 --> 01:24:17,914
We'll at least know who got the money.

1337
01:24:19,038 --> 01:24:22,165
The indictments that came down
from the grand jury today...

1338
01:24:22,166 --> 01:24:26,878
...stop with the five burglars,
Hunt and Liddy.

1339
01:24:26,879 --> 01:24:30,965
Carl, we have got to go back there and get
that bookkeeper to say who the names are.

1340
01:24:30,966 --> 01:24:32,592
She ain't gonna give it to you.

1341
01:24:32,593 --> 01:24:35,219
- I was with the woman for six hours.
- We gotta try.

1342
01:24:35,220 --> 01:24:37,388
Then you have to trick her, threaten her.

1343
01:24:37,389 --> 01:24:40,722
- Wait, you know what we could do?
- What?

1344
01:24:43,228 --> 01:24:46,105
- Listen, we go back there...
- Yeah.

1345
01:24:46,106 --> 01:24:47,899
...and you ask her who P is.

1346
01:24:47,900 --> 01:24:49,150
- Yeah.
- And then I say:

1347
01:24:49,151 --> 01:24:51,694
"No, no, no, we know P is Porter."
I just bury it.

1348
01:24:51,695 --> 01:24:54,280
- Wait a minute. I say to her, "Who is P?"
- Right.

1349
01:24:54,281 --> 01:24:57,241
- Then you say to me...
- I say, "No, we know P is Porter."

1350
01:24:57,242 --> 01:24:59,077
- You try to fake her out?
- Right.

1351
01:24:59,078 --> 01:25:00,912
And what if she denies it?

1352
01:25:00,913 --> 01:25:02,246
- We're screwed.
- So?

1353
01:25:02,247 --> 01:25:07,047
- But if she doesn't, we know P is Porter.
- Try it.

1354
01:25:15,636 --> 01:25:19,097
- Hi.
- They'll see you.

1355
01:25:19,098 --> 01:25:21,599
Not if you let us in, they won't.

1356
01:25:21,600 --> 01:25:24,435
- I'm Bob Woodward.
- They'll see your car.

1357
01:25:24,436 --> 01:25:27,438
We parked around the corner.

1358
01:25:27,439 --> 01:25:30,316
You have answers for everything,
don't you?

1359
01:25:30,317 --> 01:25:33,445
If we did, we wouldn't be here.

1360
01:25:34,947 --> 01:25:36,322
You wrote what I told you.

1361
01:25:36,323 --> 01:25:38,449
No, not your name.
No one knows it was you.

1362
01:25:38,450 --> 01:25:43,250
Could you tell us who got the money?
And how much?

1363
01:25:43,622 --> 01:25:47,208
You mean like,
"What did you do with the 25 grand, lady?"

1364
01:25:47,209 --> 01:25:48,952
What?

1365
01:25:49,211 --> 01:25:53,297
Little jokes they're making
down at Finance these days.

1366
01:25:53,298 --> 01:25:56,509
If people are to be convinced
that Stans and Sloan are innocent...

1367
01:25:56,510 --> 01:25:59,554
...then our reporting must be precise,
and you can help us.

1368
01:25:59,555 --> 01:26:01,639
- Who is P?
- P, we know, is Porter.

1369
01:26:01,640 --> 01:26:06,440
You said 25 grand.
Is that how much Porter got?

1370
01:26:10,149 --> 01:26:11,533
Was it more?

1371
01:26:16,488 --> 01:26:19,616
Was it more than $50,000?

1372
01:26:22,244 --> 01:26:25,321
Was Magruder the only M
to receive money?

1373
01:26:32,463 --> 01:26:34,513
Who told you about Porter?

1374
01:26:36,717 --> 01:26:41,345
I'd like to move on to the
subject of the break-in at the Watergate...

1375
01:26:41,346 --> 01:26:43,723
...and the controversies
coming up out of that.

1376
01:26:43,724 --> 01:26:47,226
It has recently, very recently,
been reported now...

1377
01:26:47,227 --> 01:26:51,731
...that some documents were torn up
at the Committee to Reelect the President.

1378
01:26:51,732 --> 01:26:54,692
Uh, are you investigating the tearing up
of those documents...?

1379
01:26:54,693 --> 01:26:57,528
I think that came out
in the story in the Washington Post.

1380
01:26:57,529 --> 01:26:59,530
- Yes.
- I think the investigation...

1381
01:26:59,531 --> 01:27:03,701
...that has just concluded itself has
probably been one of the most intensive...

1382
01:27:03,702 --> 01:27:07,705
...that the Department of Justice
and the FBI has ever been involved in.

1383
01:27:07,706 --> 01:27:09,957
Some 1500 persons were interviewed...

1384
01:27:09,958 --> 01:27:14,128
...1800 leads were followed,
333 agents were involved...

1385
01:27:14,129 --> 01:27:16,506
...14,000 man-hours.

1386
01:27:16,507 --> 01:27:21,307
Fifty-one of the 59 FBI field officers
were involved. Uh....

1387
01:27:21,553 --> 01:27:23,513
And that, I think...

1388
01:27:23,514 --> 01:27:27,558
...is a great credit
to justice in this country.

1389
01:27:27,559 --> 01:27:29,936
Did you know that documents
had been destroyed?

1390
01:27:29,937 --> 01:27:31,269
No, I did not.

1391
01:27:33,649 --> 01:27:37,735
All these neat little houses
on all these nice little streets.

1392
01:27:37,736 --> 01:27:40,613
It's hard to believe
that something's wrong...

1393
01:27:40,614 --> 01:27:42,657
...in some of those little houses.

1394
01:27:42,658 --> 01:27:44,708
No, it isn't.

1395
01:27:45,702 --> 01:27:48,287
- Hello. I'm Bob Woodward.
- Hello. I'm Carl Bernstein.

1396
01:27:48,288 --> 01:27:51,165
We'd just like to talk to Mr. Sloan
for a couple minutes.

1397
01:27:51,166 --> 01:27:54,478
- He's resting right now.
- Are you Mrs. Sloan?

1398
01:27:55,504 --> 01:27:59,093
- You're the two from the Post, aren't you?
- Yes.

1399
01:27:59,341 --> 01:28:04,141
- This is an honest house.
- That's why we'd like to see your husband.

1400
01:28:04,346 --> 01:28:08,766
In the face of charges that might be brought
against people that are innocent, we feel...

1401
01:28:08,767 --> 01:28:10,424
It's really for his benefit.

1402
01:28:10,644 --> 01:28:13,054
No, it's not.

1403
01:28:15,357 --> 01:28:17,100
No.

1404
01:28:17,276 --> 01:28:19,944
- It's not.
- Deborah?

1405
01:28:19,945 --> 01:28:22,446
- Tell them to come in.
- Thanks.

1406
01:28:22,447 --> 01:28:24,824
- Hi. Carl Bernstein.
- How do you do? Hugh Sloan.

1407
01:28:24,825 --> 01:28:26,033
Bob Woodward.

1408
01:28:26,034 --> 01:28:30,115
- How you doing? Hugh Sloan.
- I appreciate you giving us the time.

1409
01:28:36,086 --> 01:28:40,381
You know, the reason we're here, basically,
is that we talked to certain people...

1410
01:28:40,382 --> 01:28:42,508
...who indicated you left the committee...

1411
01:28:42,509 --> 01:28:44,969
...because you no longer wanted
to be part of it.

1412
01:28:44,970 --> 01:28:47,013
Maybe there's a legitimate explanation...

1413
01:28:47,014 --> 01:28:51,066
...for why the money was handed
to Liddy and Mitchell's aides.

1414
01:28:53,562 --> 01:28:56,125
Try and understand this.

1415
01:28:56,815 --> 01:28:59,609
- I'm a Republican.
- I am too.

1416
01:28:59,610 --> 01:29:01,444
Well, I believe in Richard Nixon.

1417
01:29:01,445 --> 01:29:04,614
I worked in the White House for four years,
and so did my wife.

1418
01:29:04,615 --> 01:29:06,824
What happened on June 17th...

1419
01:29:06,825 --> 01:29:09,327
...I don't think the president
knew anything about.

1420
01:29:09,328 --> 01:29:11,829
Is it possible some of his people
might have known?

1421
01:29:11,830 --> 01:29:13,039
I'm not sure.

1422
01:29:13,040 --> 01:29:14,916
Think the truth will come out at the trial?

1423
01:29:14,917 --> 01:29:17,209
- That's another thing I'm not sure about.
- Why?

1424
01:29:17,210 --> 01:29:19,921
Obviously because certain people
lie to the prosecutor.

1425
01:29:19,922 --> 01:29:22,173
No, we were never told flat-out,
"Don't talk."

1426
01:29:22,174 --> 01:29:24,175
But the message was clear, though.

1427
01:29:24,176 --> 01:29:27,094
In other words, by their very silence,
there was a cover-up.

1428
01:29:27,095 --> 01:29:29,847
They didn't urge us to come forward
and tell the truth.

1429
01:29:29,848 --> 01:29:32,183
"They" meaning the White House?

1430
01:29:32,184 --> 01:29:34,393
The committee's not
an independent operation.

1431
01:29:34,394 --> 01:29:36,479
Everything's cleared
with the White House.

1432
01:29:36,480 --> 01:29:39,774
And I don't think that the FBI
or the prosecutors understand that.

1433
01:29:39,775 --> 01:29:42,544
That report on the cash...

1434
01:29:42,736 --> 01:29:46,364
...in the CREEP safe, that...
What was it?... $350,000, is that a...?

1435
01:29:46,365 --> 01:29:49,283
- No, more.
- Was that a correct figure?

1436
01:29:49,284 --> 01:29:52,412
No, it was closer to 1 million.

1437
01:29:52,955 --> 01:29:55,665
And as treasurer,
you could release those funds?

1438
01:29:55,666 --> 01:29:57,833
When so ordered.

1439
01:29:57,834 --> 01:30:00,044
We don't know who could order you.

1440
01:30:00,045 --> 01:30:02,380
- We just know there were four.
- There were five.

1441
01:30:02,381 --> 01:30:05,383
- Five?
- Mitchell, Stans, Magruder, they're obvious.

1442
01:30:05,384 --> 01:30:07,843
Well, there had to be
a White House overseer.

1443
01:30:07,844 --> 01:30:09,679
- Yeah, Colson.
- What?

1444
01:30:09,680 --> 01:30:14,480
No, Colson's too smart to get involved
directly with anything like that.

1445
01:30:14,685 --> 01:30:16,632
It's Haldeman.

1446
01:30:18,689 --> 01:30:20,534
Right?

1447
01:30:21,233 --> 01:30:23,109
I won't talk about the other two.

1448
01:30:23,110 --> 01:30:25,611
- They both worked at the White House?
- One did.

1449
01:30:25,612 --> 01:30:28,698
The other one's not in Washington,
but that's all I'll say.

1450
01:30:28,699 --> 01:30:30,491
- Kalmbach.
- Nixon's personal lawyer.

1451
01:30:30,492 --> 01:30:31,742
- Yeah.
- Right?

1452
01:30:31,743 --> 01:30:35,469
- Nixon's personal lawyer?
- I can't say anything. I'm sorry.

1453
01:30:37,207 --> 01:30:39,668
- Well....
- When's the baby due?

1454
01:30:41,253 --> 01:30:44,296
Um, soon. Next month.

1455
01:30:44,297 --> 01:30:45,798
Are you gonna stay here?

1456
01:30:45,799 --> 01:30:49,093
- No, I don't think so.
- You decided where you're gonna go?

1457
01:30:49,094 --> 01:30:53,055
I've been looking for a job
in the private sector, but it's....

1458
01:30:53,056 --> 01:30:56,389
It's very hard.
My name's been in the papers too much.

1459
01:30:57,561 --> 01:31:01,105
- You know one thing I'm not clear about?
- What?

1460
01:31:01,106 --> 01:31:02,690
I don't know how... How did...?

1461
01:31:02,691 --> 01:31:05,776
When you handed out the money,
how did that work exactly?

1462
01:31:05,777 --> 01:31:08,136
Badly.

1463
01:31:11,533 --> 01:31:15,119
I think what Bob means is,
ordinarily, what was the procedure?

1464
01:31:15,120 --> 01:31:18,581
Routine. I'd call John Mitchell
over at the Justice Department.

1465
01:31:18,582 --> 01:31:23,076
- He'd say, "Go ahead, give out the money."
This was all done verbally?

1466
01:31:23,420 --> 01:31:25,111
Yes.

1467
01:31:25,213 --> 01:31:28,049
We know there were five men
who controlled the slush fund.

1468
01:31:28,050 --> 01:31:30,718
- Mitchell, Stans and Magruder.
- Those three we've got.

1469
01:31:30,719 --> 01:31:34,263
- All three have been named by two sources.
- What about the other two?

1470
01:31:34,264 --> 01:31:36,474
- Kalmbach.
- We're pretty sure of Kalmbach.

1471
01:31:36,475 --> 01:31:39,643
Maybe you'd better wait
till we get all five, huh?

1472
01:31:39,644 --> 01:31:40,853
Certain on Mitchell?

1473
01:31:40,854 --> 01:31:44,190
We know he approved payments to Liddy
while he was attorney general.

1474
01:31:44,191 --> 01:31:45,983
- You got more than one source?
- Yes.

1475
01:31:45,984 --> 01:31:47,193
- Who are they?
- Sloan.

1476
01:31:47,194 --> 01:31:48,402
Sloan and who else?

1477
01:31:48,403 --> 01:31:52,239
Another guy at Justice who won't confirm
the other two who controlled the fund.

1478
01:31:52,240 --> 01:31:54,825
- What about Deep Throat?
- He's not a source on this.

1479
01:31:54,826 --> 01:31:56,494
- Do any of them have an ax?
- Nope.

1480
01:31:56,495 --> 01:31:59,413
Personal, political, sexual?
Anything at all on Mitchell?

1481
01:31:59,414 --> 01:32:00,873
- No.
- Can we use their names?

1482
01:32:00,874 --> 01:32:02,333
- No.
- Goddamn it.

1483
01:32:02,334 --> 01:32:05,469
When is somebody gonna go on the record
in this story?

1484
01:32:08,215 --> 01:32:11,675
You are about to write a story
that says the former attorney general...

1485
01:32:11,676 --> 01:32:16,446
...the highest-ranking law-enforcement
officer in this country, is a crook.

1486
01:32:18,517 --> 01:32:21,388
Just be sure you're right.

1487
01:32:23,688 --> 01:32:26,982
- Essex House, may I help you?
- John Mitchell.

1488
01:32:34,699 --> 01:32:36,408
Yes?

1489
01:32:36,409 --> 01:32:39,036
Sir, this is Carl Bernstein
of the Washington Post...

1490
01:32:39,037 --> 01:32:41,664
...and I'm sorry to disturb you
at this hour.

1491
01:32:41,665 --> 01:32:45,251
Tomorrow we're running a story
in the paper...

1492
01:32:45,252 --> 01:32:50,052
...and we just think that you should
have a chance to comment on it.

1493
01:32:50,674 --> 01:32:52,550
What does it say?

1494
01:32:52,551 --> 01:32:57,351
"John N. Mitchell, while serving
as United States attorney general..."

1495
01:32:58,181 --> 01:33:00,933
...personally controlled
a secret cash fund...

1496
01:33:00,934 --> 01:33:03,519
...used to gather information
about the Democrats...

1497
01:33:03,520 --> 01:33:07,064
"...according to sources involved
in the Watergate investigation."

1498
01:33:07,065 --> 01:33:09,942
- Jesus.
- "Beginning in the spring of 1971..."

1499
01:33:09,943 --> 01:33:12,403
...a year before
he left the Justice Department...

1500
01:33:12,404 --> 01:33:14,822
...to become President Nixon's
campaign manager.

1501
01:33:14,823 --> 01:33:19,201
"On March 1, Mitchell personally approved
withdrawals from the fund."

1502
01:33:19,202 --> 01:33:21,787
All that crap,
you're putting it in the paper?

1503
01:33:21,788 --> 01:33:24,665
- Well...
- Look, it's all been denied.

1504
01:33:24,666 --> 01:33:26,750
Tell your publisher, tell Katie Graham...

1505
01:33:26,751 --> 01:33:30,129
...she's gonna get her tit caught
in a big ringer if that's published.

1506
01:33:30,130 --> 01:33:32,756
Christ, that's the most sickening thing
I ever heard.

1507
01:33:32,757 --> 01:33:36,010
- I wonder if I could ask you some questions.
- What time is it?

1508
01:33:36,011 --> 01:33:38,179
It's 11:30, sir.

1509
01:33:38,180 --> 01:33:40,306
Eleven-thirty?

1510
01:33:40,307 --> 01:33:43,642
- Is it morning or night?
- It's 11:30 at night, sir.

1511
01:33:43,643 --> 01:33:46,645
- Oh.
- Sir, the Committee to Reelect...

1512
01:33:46,646 --> 01:33:50,608
...has issued a statement to our story,
but there are a couple questions...

1513
01:33:50,609 --> 01:33:53,819
Did the committee tell you
to go ahead and publish the story?

1514
01:33:53,820 --> 01:33:56,572
You fellas have a great ball game going.

1515
01:33:56,573 --> 01:34:00,284
As soon as you're done,
we're gonna do a story on all of you.

1516
01:34:00,285 --> 01:34:05,085
- Sir, there's just a couple of questions...
- Call my law office in the morning.

1517
01:34:06,917 --> 01:34:09,627
There's no question
you properly identified yourself?

1518
01:34:09,628 --> 01:34:12,140
Said it right off the top.

1519
01:34:12,923 --> 01:34:17,676
- Mitchell know he was talking to a reporter?
- Yeah, but I think I woke him up.

1520
01:34:17,677 --> 01:34:21,267
- You have good notes?
- Verbatim.

1521
01:34:21,473 --> 01:34:25,165
He really said that about Mrs. Graham?

1522
01:34:25,769 --> 01:34:27,937
Well, cut the words "her tit" and print it.

1523
01:34:27,938 --> 01:34:31,271
- Why?
- This is a family newspaper.

1524
01:34:34,444 --> 01:34:35,903
Once when I was reporting...

1525
01:34:35,904 --> 01:34:38,989
...Lyndon Johnson's top guy
gave me the word...

1526
01:34:38,990 --> 01:34:42,243
...they were looking for a successor
for J. Edgar Hoover.

1527
01:34:42,244 --> 01:34:46,121
I wrote it, and the day it appeared,
Johnson held a press conference...

1528
01:34:46,122 --> 01:34:49,625
...and appointed Hoover
head of the FBI for life.

1529
01:34:49,626 --> 01:34:52,336
When he was done,
he turned to his top guy...

1530
01:34:52,337 --> 01:34:55,703
...and the president said,
"Call Ben Bradlee and tell him, 'Fuck you."'

1531
01:34:56,716 --> 01:34:59,385
Then everybody said,
"You did it, Ben. You screwed up.

1532
01:34:59,386 --> 01:35:02,596
You stuck us with Hoover forever."

1533
01:35:02,597 --> 01:35:04,390
I screwed up...

1534
01:35:04,391 --> 01:35:07,571
...but I wasn't wrong. Hm.

1535
01:35:09,187 --> 01:35:12,674
How much can you tell me
about Deep Throat?

1536
01:35:13,149 --> 01:35:15,317
How much do you need to know?

1537
01:35:15,318 --> 01:35:17,523
Do you trust him?

1538
01:35:18,738 --> 01:35:20,533
Yeah.

1539
01:35:22,033 --> 01:35:26,833
I can't do the reporting for my reporters,
which means I have to trust them.

1540
01:35:28,290 --> 01:35:31,725
And I hate trusting anybody.

1541
01:35:38,800 --> 01:35:41,363
Run that baby.

1542
01:36:20,050 --> 01:36:24,261
The Washington Post reported
that while still in office as attorney general...

1543
01:36:24,262 --> 01:36:28,599
...John Mitchell had personally controlled
a secret Republican fund.

1544
01:36:28,600 --> 01:36:32,728
Mitchell denied any such involvement
and called the story "ludicrous."

1545
01:36:32,729 --> 01:36:36,231
The new charge also brought a response
from Vice President Agnew...

1546
01:36:36,232 --> 01:36:37,775
...at his stop in Tampa.

1547
01:36:37,776 --> 01:36:41,362
I have full confidence in Mr. Mitchell...

1548
01:36:41,363 --> 01:36:44,490
...and in the people
in the Republican organization...

1549
01:36:44,491 --> 01:36:48,452
...and I think that
that kind of unattributed report...

1550
01:36:48,453 --> 01:36:51,622
...at a time like this is counterproductive.

1551
01:36:51,623 --> 01:36:56,293
We must bear in mind
that those who published it...

1552
01:36:56,294 --> 01:36:59,588
...have already shown their sympathy
for the other ticket.

1553
01:36:59,589 --> 01:37:02,674
- A band and some young cheerleaders...
- All non-denial denials.

1554
01:37:02,675 --> 01:37:06,053
They doubt our ancestry,
but they don't say the story isn't accurate.

1555
01:37:06,054 --> 01:37:08,180
Did you understand
one thing he was saying?

1556
01:37:08,181 --> 01:37:11,141
What I can't figure out is,
what is a real denial?

1557
01:37:11,142 --> 01:37:15,354
Well, if they start calling us goddamn liars,
we better start circling the wagons.

1558
01:37:15,355 --> 01:37:18,769
- When you think they'll start doing that?
- When they get out of Tampa.

1559
01:37:20,151 --> 01:37:22,820
Joe, come on,
what's going on with you guys at the FBI?

1560
01:37:22,821 --> 01:37:26,156
I've been trying to get you for weeks.
Secretary says you're not in.

1561
01:37:26,157 --> 01:37:28,158
Last night, you said you couldn't talk.

1562
01:37:28,159 --> 01:37:30,994
This morning,
soon as our Mitchell story hits the stands...

1563
01:37:30,995 --> 01:37:33,622
...you call and say you gotta see me
right away. Why?

1564
01:37:33,623 --> 01:37:36,208
You guys have been causing big trouble
at the bureau.

1565
01:37:36,209 --> 01:37:37,584
Why?

1566
01:37:37,585 --> 01:37:41,130
Our reports are showing up
in your paper almost verbatim.

1567
01:37:41,131 --> 01:37:44,967
I mean, you've really been on the mark,
except for Mitchell.

1568
01:37:44,968 --> 01:37:47,344
Now, we didn't have that...

1569
01:37:47,345 --> 01:37:49,012
...that he controlled the funds.

1570
01:37:49,013 --> 01:37:50,514
Right.

1571
01:37:50,515 --> 01:37:52,307
Our agents have been busting ass...

1572
01:37:52,308 --> 01:37:55,102
...but we're gonna go back
and see if we missed anything.

1573
01:37:55,103 --> 01:37:58,772
What I don't understand is all the people
who know details of the bugging...

1574
01:37:58,773 --> 01:38:00,482
...the FBI hasn't even talked to.

1575
01:38:00,483 --> 01:38:04,194
Why have you conducted interviews of
CREEP personnel at CREEP headquarters...

1576
01:38:04,195 --> 01:38:07,448
...instead of at their homes,
where they might feel freer to talk?

1577
01:38:07,449 --> 01:38:08,699
Joe, wait a minute.

1578
01:38:08,700 --> 01:38:11,535
Why have the interviews at CREEP
always been conducted...

1579
01:38:11,536 --> 01:38:14,371
...within the presence of the lawyer
who works for CREEP?

1580
01:38:14,372 --> 01:38:17,207
Look, you know,
I can't answer for the whole bureau.

1581
01:38:17,208 --> 01:38:21,106
- Oh, come on, I'm just...
- I do what I'm told.

1582
01:38:21,546 --> 01:38:24,520
I followed my orders, period.

1583
01:38:29,929 --> 01:38:32,134
What orders?

1584
01:38:35,185 --> 01:38:39,339
Woodward! Woodward!

1585
01:38:40,064 --> 01:38:41,859
Wait!

1586
01:38:42,484 --> 01:38:44,277
Bob!

1587
01:38:46,488 --> 01:38:50,334
Out of the blue. Out of the blue.

1588
01:38:50,992 --> 01:38:54,369
This morning I get a tip
to call a guy by the name of Alex Shipley...

1589
01:38:54,370 --> 01:38:57,206
...who is now the assistant attorney general
of Tennessee.

1590
01:38:57,207 --> 01:38:59,625
Now, the guy told me that called me...
That said...

1591
01:38:59,626 --> 01:39:02,336
He said that Shipley was asked
in the summer of 1971...

1592
01:39:02,337 --> 01:39:04,880
...by an old Army buddy,
a Donald Segretti...

1593
01:39:04,881 --> 01:39:06,840
...to join a group of other lawyers...

1594
01:39:06,841 --> 01:39:09,885
...for Nixon's campaign
to sabotage the Democratic candidates.

1595
01:39:09,886 --> 01:39:13,180
- Make a left. We'll go to my place.
- Sabotage Democratic candidates?

1596
01:39:13,181 --> 01:39:17,226
I was able to make a couple calls,
and I got Segretti's records for the year...

1597
01:39:17,227 --> 01:39:20,812
His travel records for the year 1971-'72.

1598
01:39:20,813 --> 01:39:22,022
Does the FBI know...?

1599
01:39:22,023 --> 01:39:24,191
- Did you say left or right?
- Left, my place.

1600
01:39:24,192 --> 01:39:27,486
- We gotta go through the records.
- Does the FBI know about Segretti?

1601
01:39:27,487 --> 01:39:30,781
FBI interrogated Segretti,
found he wasn't involved in the break-in.

1602
01:39:30,782 --> 01:39:32,783
They dropped it, didn't follow through.

1603
01:39:32,784 --> 01:39:34,952
- Where is he?
- He's in California.

1604
01:39:34,953 --> 01:39:36,620
- Jesus, look at this.
- What?

1605
01:39:36,621 --> 01:39:40,229
Segretti crisscrossed the country
at least a dozen times.

1606
01:39:42,126 --> 01:39:45,087
Only stayed in cities
where there were Democratic primaries.

1607
01:39:45,088 --> 01:39:47,130
If the break-in was just one incident...

1608
01:39:47,131 --> 01:39:49,925
...in a campaign of sabotage
that began a year before....

1609
01:39:49,926 --> 01:39:52,135
For the first time,
the break-in makes sense.

1610
01:39:52,136 --> 01:39:53,345
This isn't so crazy.

1611
01:39:53,346 --> 01:39:55,639
This whole thing didn't start
with the bugging.

1612
01:39:55,640 --> 01:39:58,100
Segretti was doing this
a year before the bugging.

1613
01:39:58,101 --> 01:40:00,811
And a year before,
Nixon was running behind Muskie...

1614
01:40:00,812 --> 01:40:03,632
...before Muskie self-destructed.

1615
01:40:03,898 --> 01:40:06,257
If he self-destructed.

1616
01:40:06,693 --> 01:40:09,528
- Hi. Uh, Donald Segretti?
- That's right.

1617
01:40:09,529 --> 01:40:12,990
I'm Carl Bernstein
from the Washington Post.

1618
